hn Yau, along with its analysis of a new archive of Asian American writers from the 1970s, this book is indispensable for readers interested in race, Asian American studies, contemporary poetry, and the avant-garde.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / Asian American.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478822940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804788229423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804788229/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles